name: sphinx-autobuild
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "sphinx-autobuild" %}
{% set version = "2021.3.14" %}

package:
  name: {{ name }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: de1ca3b66e271d2b5b5140c35034c89e47f263f2cd5db302c9217065f7443f05

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install --no-deps --ignore-installed .
  entry_points:
    - sphinx-autobuild=sphinx_autobuild.__main__:main

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.6
    - flit

  run:
    - python >=3.6
    - sphinx
    - livereload >=2.3.0

test:
  requires:
    - pytest
    - mock

  imports:
    - sphinx_autobuild

  source_files:
    - tests

  commands:
    - sphinx-autobuild --help
    - pytest tests

about:
  home: https://github.com/executablebooks/sphinx-autobuild
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Watch a Sphinx directory and rebuild the documentation when a change is detected. Also includes a livereload enabled web server.


extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jrderuiter
    - xhochy
